The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, which are typically categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of functions and sets in the paper also suggests a possible categorization under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of proper edge colorings and spectra of vertices in graphs may also fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the use of parameters and optimization in the paper may suggest a possible categorization under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
